Power BI Steps:

# Data Set upload: Go to get data ---> Choose the Data set D:\Elevate Labs\HR Analytics - Predict Employee Attrition\Data set 
--> Transform data if need to add any columns or load the cleaned data. 

Phase 1: Adding Conditional Column

Go to Home ‚Üí Transform Data (Power Query Editor).
Click Add Column ‚Üí Conditional Column.
Configure:
New column name: Attrition_Count
Column name: Attrition
Operator: equals
Value: "Yes"
Output: 1
Else: 0
Click OK.

Created a helper column Attrition_Count in Power Query using conditional logic (Yes = 1, No = 0) to enable attrition rate calculations and KPI analysis.

Phase 2: Key Metrics (DAX Measures) in Power BI:

Step 1: Create a Measures Table
Create New Table (for organizing measures)
Go to Modeling ‚Üí New Table and write:
_Measures = { "Key Metrics" }

After creating it:
Hide the column.
Create all measures inside this _Measures table.

Created a dedicated _Measures table to centrally manage all KPI DAX measures for better dashboard organization and model clarity.

Step 2: Create DAX Measures
Go to Modeling ‚Üí New Measure and create the following:

1Ô∏è‚É£ Total Employees
Total Employees = COUNTROWS('Table')

Project Note:
Calculated total employee count using COUNTROWS to determine overall workforce size.

2Ô∏è‚É£ Attrition Count
Attrition Count =
CALCULATE(
    [Total Employees],
    'Table'[Attrition] = "Yes"
)

Project Note:
Computed total attrition cases using CALCULATE with filter condition (Attrition = "Yes").

3Ô∏è‚É£ Attrition Rate (%)
Attrition Rate =
DIVIDE(
    [Attrition Count],
    [Total Employees],
    0
)

After creating:
Change format ‚Üí Percentage.

Project Note:
Derived attrition rate by dividing attrition count by total employees using DIVIDE for safe error handling.

4Ô∏è‚É£ Average Tenure
Avg Tenure = AVERAGE('Table'[YearsAtCompany])

Project Note:
Calculated average employee tenure using AVERAGE function on YearsAtCompany column.

Go to Modeling ‚Üí New Measure and write:
Active Employees = [Total Employees] - [Attrition Count]

Project Note:
Calculated Active Employees by subtracting attrition count from total employees to represent the current workforce strength for KPI monitoring.

Why This Structure Is Important.

COUNTROWS ‚Üí Base workforce metric
CALCULATE ‚Üí Applies filter context
DIVIDE ‚Üí Prevents divide-by-zero errors
Measures table ‚Üí Best practice for clean data modeling

